When Fortnum & Mason first opened their doors nearly 250 years ago in 1710, Queen Anne held court at Kensington Palace, and the American Republic was still a half century away from its being born. The life and times of this period still remain with us in the works of William Congreve, Addison & Steele, Jonathan Swift, and Alexander Pope.
